parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Relay and Wiring Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay and wiring can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
and overheated or melted wiring in the trunk fuse box.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights and brake lights can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the ESC system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the EPS system can cause the power steering to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering warning light comes on
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the ESC (Electronic Stability Control) system is disabled
and the traction control warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column torque sensor can cause the power steering system to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering warning light comes on
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle is difficult to steer
and the traction control warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose stability and control, leading to an increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ESC warning light comes on
the traction control warning light is illuminated
and the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion can cause the power steering system to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the power steering warning light comes on
and the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the low beam headlights can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to traffic violations.
symptoms: The low beam headlights fail to operate
often without warning. The issue can occur on either the driver's side or passenger's side

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system related to the headlight circuit can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlights may not turn on
often due to issues with the wiring harness

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Light and ESC System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light and ESC system can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights may not turn on
often accompanied by issues with the ESC system
such as the "Service ESC" warning light.
